13/08/2010
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) police have arrested five people suspected of ties to the radical Islam Wahhabi movement. 
The RS Interior Ministry confirmed the arrests on Thursday (August 12th) and said they were made based on illegal weapons possession. 
The suspects were detained in Kozarska Dubica and Novi Grad. 
(Glas Javnosti, Nezavisne Novine - 12/08/10)
